  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "# Feature Issue\n### User Story\nAs a user I want to enter my transfer amount in fiat, because I don't know what the current token value is. Also, I determine how much I want to transfer in fiat, as it's most familiar due to day to day use.\n\n### Description\nDesigns on [Figma](https://www.figma.com/file/XUehMnhyD1FGcWzvGz6SXqvh/Wallet?node-id=5849%3A42299)\n\n* [ ] Designs change the asset selection to become a list item below the divider\n* [ ] The default selected asset remains ETH (no change)\n* [ ] Designs introduce a new button style `Enter in USD`\n* [ ] Currency displayed on the button depends on the set default fiat currency\n* [ ] When button `Enter in USD` is tapped:\n* [ ]  Button copy changes to `Enter in SNT` (depending on selected asset, ETH as default)\n* [ ]  Asset/currency label by Amount field is updated\n* [ ]  Asset icon is updated\n* [ ] When amount is entered:\n* [ ] Converted value changes from 0 to entered value\n\n![Frame 2](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35233054/75549624-635a1700-5a30-11ea-831b-abe24e4b1f2a.png)\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\nImplementation follows design\n\n### Notes\nSee also issue to add `Send all` next to `Enter in USD` https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/10105\n\n",
